data.reddit:
Female, 
21, 
190 lbs, 
history of endometriosis and anxiety. 
Location legs, 
Currently taking lexapro, ferrograd c and preconception vitamins. 

It doesn’t always happen but it’s enough to make me have a shitty sleep and I guess I’m just wondering why it’s happening. 

Sometimes right when I’m falling asleep my legs will ache a lot, feels exactly like growing pains. (I get the same pain in my wrists too but that’s irrelevant probably). The pain is so awful and irritating that I’ll often just exhaust myself and fall asleep, but then during my sleep it’s kind of like my legs jolt. The best way I can describe it is like when you hit that one spot on your knee and it makes your entire leg jolt, and it’s not really painful but really uncomfortable through your whole leg. That’s basically what it feels like. 

This happens at least 10 times a night. I’ve been having issues with my gp only lately where little things like this just are kind of trivial to him and sometimes he will make fun of me and I never get tested for anything anymore and i guess I’m just nervous to talk about my little concerns like this and figured asking here could ease my mind. 

I have a feeling it’s probably just some form of anxiety problem but yeah.
